= Microsoft Patent Strategy: 10 patent applications per day =

An [http://www.eweek.com/article2/0,1759,1566299,00.asp article in E-Week] says that Microsoft has lost billions through patent lawsuits in recent years but
meanwhile has built a sizeable patent portfolio which is has been growing by 3 patents per week for the last few years and has now reached a speed of 10 patents per day.  The purpose of these patents, according to the article, is to prevent interoperation with Microsoft's next operating system version.

Microsoft is a [http://www.eu2004.ie/sitetools/sponsorship.asp sponsor of the Irish EU Presidency] and pushing for [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/europarl0309/cons0401/ unlimited patentability of computer-implemented algorithms and business methods] in Europe.

 * [http://www.aful.org/wws/arc/patents/2004-05/msg00015.html Bernard Lang on Microsoft strategy and Irish presidency]
 * [http://swpat.ffii.org/players/microsoft/ Microsoft]
 * [http://swpat.ffii.org/players/ie/ Ireland]
